Review_body:
There is a documentary about the family of a missing child that found him years later, in France. When they found him, he's now a teenager, he's traumatized, and he didn't t talk much. It turned out he was an imposter - a 30-something year old ex-convict and con-man that worked the system in several countries. He depended on bad record keeping, human laziness, and the desperation of the family. 'The Imposter' (2012).This is a well-executed and unique horror tale. There probably should have been more sexuality, but the actress, Isabelle Fuhrman, is way underage at the time of filming. Despite the lack of actual sex, Isabelle Fuhrman carries the film and is the definition of outstanding; considering Vera Farmiga is the lead actress, Isabelle's performance is quite an accomplishment.RealReview Posting Scoring Criteria:
Acting - 1/1;
Casting - 1/1;
Directing - 1/1;
Story - 1/1;
Writing/Screenplay - 1/1;Total Base Score = 5Modifiers (+ or -):
Standout Performances: +1 ( Isabelle Fuhrman );Total RealReview Rating: 6

Story-line => 3/5 (The plot was turning out to be interesting one in the beginning but as the movie progress it is not much different from a common horror movie except, unlike common horror movies they tried to build up a plot that makes sense.);
Acting => 5/5 (The acting should get a round of applause especially Esther's acting.);
Directing => 3/5 (This is a well-made one but cliche.);
Visual Effects/Animation => 5/5 (Enough for the story.);
Screenplay => 3/5 (The screenplay was a bit bland if we consider everything.);
Personal Recommendation => 4/5 (This is obviously not a traditional horror movie. Even if you dislike horror movies, you can watch it. If you're looking for a perfect storyline, you might get a bit disappointed. But it is worth watching.);
Most Favorite Character => Kate (as a character of a responsible mother who is trying to do the right thing), Esther(her acting was praiseworthy);
